{"updated_at": {"date": {"d": "02", "m": "07", "Y": "2026"}, "time": {"H": "06", "M": "58", "S": "22"}}, "news": [{"title": "Over 270 Bengaluru development body's sites to soon get relief; 55 still in limbo", "para": "Over 250 site owners in Banashankari 6th Phase, Bengaluru, are set to gain relief from a long-standing Turahalli forest buffer zone dispute. The Bangalore Development Authority (BDA) has proposed a one-time settlement with the forest department, aiming to grant full possession of legally allotted sites. This move follows years of uncertainty, with surveys narrowing down the affected properties.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/bda-offers-relief-to-250-site-owners-in-banashankari-6th-phase-amid-forest-dispute/132128737?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-3791983/132128737.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}, {"title": "Maharashtra: New co-op housing society rules include online AGMs, 12% interest cap on maintenance arrears", "para": "Maharashtra housing societies can now hold annual meetings online, and interest on maintenance arrears is capped at 12% annually. New rules, notified Tuesday, provide a dedicated legal framework for societies, covering registration, membership, redevelopment, and financial management. These reforms aim to streamline operations and enhance governance, with model bylaws expected soon to ensure uniformity across the state.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/residential/maharashtra-implements-new-housing-society-rules-online-agms-and-interest-caps-on-maintenance/132128706?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-557020/132128706.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "residential"}, {"title": "Ahmedabad civic body looks to monetise over 209 properties", "para": "Ahmedabad Municipal Corporation is launching an ambitious asset monetisation drive, targeting over 200 civic properties including gardens, schools, and community halls.  A consultant has been appointed to explore revenue generation through amusement parks, food courts, and private management of facilities.  The initiative aims to unlock the value of properties estimated at over Rs 2,000 crore, with plans to rent out school buildings and allow private buses on BRTS corridors.", "href": "https://realty.economictimes.indiatimes.com/news/industry/ahmedabad-civic-body-plans-to-monetise-over-209-properties-to-generate-revenue/132128602?utm_source=newslisting&utm_medium=latestNews", "img": "data:image/png;base64, ", "img-src": "https://etimg.etb2bimg.com/thumb/img-size-2627458/132128602.cms?width=150&height=112", "tag": "industry"}]}